H.K. Chief Secretary Tang’s Resignation Approved, Xinhua Reports

-- B y   M a r c o   L u i
-- 
2011-09-30T02:57:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/h-k-chief-secretary-tang-s-resignation-approved-xinhua-reports.html
China’s State Council approved Hong
Kong Chief Secretary Henry Tang’s resignation and appointed
Secretary for Constitutional and Mainland Affairs Stephen Lam as
Tang’s successor, Xinhua News Agency reported today.  Raymond Tam will take over Lam’s position, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Lui at 
 mlui11@bloomberg.net  